cp\u003e‘It is better to use builder\u0026#39;s sand or pea gravel, as these can provide better airflow than other materials when used as mulch. Avoid materials like fine sand, as this can clump together easily and may make it harder for water to reach the roots of the lavender,’ says Graham.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAdding sand or gravel is not to be confused with fertilising your plant, as lavender doesn’t require much fertilising anyway, as it prefers poor soil. This method improves the drainage of your soil so your lavender can thrive. This achieves beautiful purple flowers as a result.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSo, if you want to get the most out of your lavender plant, consider adding a layer of sand or gravel to its base. You’ll be rewarded with the prettiest, fragrant flowers.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"section-shop-gravel-and-sand\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eShop gravel and sand\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv data-id=\"ff27ceef-1598-4677-bf30-ca6b65c17553\"\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://target.georiot.com/Proxy.ashx?tsid=107653\u0026amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Famazon.co.uk%2FVitax-Horticultural-Potting-Gravel-Small%2Fdp%2FB07BJZBF8G%2Fref%3Dasc_df_B07BJZBF8G%3Fmcid%3D82600d3c4bc439e68b20f568123e44b5%26linkCode%3Ddf0%26hvadid%3D697221579505%26hvpos%3D%26hvnetw%3Dg%26hvrand%3D17909503398331914978%26hvpone%3D%26hvptwo%3D%26hvqmt%3D%26hvdev%3Dc%26hvdvcmdl%3D%26hvlocint%3D%26hvlocphy%3D9045622%26hvtargid%3Dpla-1490475367840%26psc%3D1%26hvocijid%3D17909503398331914978-B07BJZBF8G-%26hvexpln%3D0%26gad_source%3D1%26tag%3Dhawk-future-21%26ascsubtag%3Didealhome-gb-1037121615884166095-21\" data-model-name=\"Vitax Horticulture Grit Small\" data-url=\"https://www.amazon.co.uk/Vitax-Horticultural-Potting-Gravel-Small/dp/B07BJZBF8G/ref=asc_df_B07BJZBF8G?mcid=82600d3c4bc439e68b20f568123e44b5\u0026amp;tag=googshopuk-21\u0026amp;linkCode=df0\u0026amp;hvadid=697221579505\u0026amp;hvpos=\u0026amp;hvnetw=g\u0026amp;hvrand=17909503398331914978\u0026amp;hvpone=\u